---
import Layout from '../layouts/BlogPost.astro';
---

<Layout
  title="Portfolio"
  description="Selected projects and work by Principal Full-Stack Engineer Eric Carlisle."
  pageType="portfolio"
>
  <header class="portfolio-hero">
    <p class="lede">
      I design and build enterprise software systems that turn complex product,
      data, and platform problems into maintainable user experiences.
    </p>
    <p>
      My work spans healthcare, digital media, retail and digital commerce, and
      platform engineering, with a focus on frontend architecture, UX
      engineering, integration layers, performance, accessibility, and scalable
      delivery.
    </p>
    <p class="portfolio-note">
      Many of these projects were delivered inside enterprise environments where
      source code and internal systems cannot be publicly shared. These case
      studies focus on architecture, constraints, product decisions, and
      outcomes rather than proprietary implementation details.
    </p>
  </header>

  <section id="case-studies" class="case-studies">
    <h2>Selected Case Studies</h2>

    <article class="case-study">
      <div class="case-study-overview">
        <h3>Scaling Multi-Tenant Frontend Systems</h3>
        <p class="meta">
          <strong>Principal Software Engineer</strong>
          Arc XP &middot; Digital Media / Publishing Platform &middot; 2018-2022
        </p>
        <p>
          Architected reusable frontend patterns and platform standards across
          enterprise publishing environments supporting many client
          implementations.
        </p>
        <p>
          Focused on creating systems that balanced flexibility and governance
          while improving delivery velocity and maintaining performance at
          scale.
        </p>
      </div>
      <div class="case-study-details">
        <div>
          <h4>Focus areas</h4>
          <div class="tags">
            <span class="tag">React</span>
            <span class="tag">Component Architecture</span>
            <span class="tag">Design Systems</span>
            <span class="tag">Performance</span>
            <span class="tag">Migration</span>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div>
          <h4>Highlights</h4>
          <ul>
            <li>Designed reusable frontend architecture patterns</li>
            <li>Supported large-scale platform migrations</li>
            <li>Improved maintainability across multi-tenant environments</li>
            <li>Bridged engineering and design system implementation</li>
          </ul>
        </div>
      </div>
    </article>

    <article class="case-study">
      <div class="case-study-overview">
        <h3>Reengineering Enterprise Commerce Performance</h3>
        <p class="meta">
          <strong>Senior UX Engineer</strong>
          Under Armour &middot; Retail / Digital Commerce
        </p>
        <p>
          Led UI optimization efforts during a major site reengineering
          initiative focused on improving customer experience, delivery quality,
          and frontend performance.
        </p>
        <p>
          This engagement emphasized measurable business outcomes through
          architecture simplification, performance tuning, and experience
          improvements.
        </p>
      </div>
      <div class="case-study-details">
        <div>
          <h4>Focus areas</h4>
          <div class="tags">
            <span class="tag">Performance</span>
            <span class="tag">UX Engineering</span>
            <span class="tag">Optimization</span>
            <span class="tag">Accessibility</span>
            <span class="tag">Delivery</span>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div>
          <h4>Highlights</h4>
          <ul>
            <li>Modernized frontend implementation approaches</li>
            <li>Improved customer experience through targeted optimization</li>
            <li>Balanced business priorities with technical constraints</li>
            <li>Established scalable patterns for future development</li>
          </ul>
        </div>
      </div>
    </article>

    <article class="case-study">
      <div class="case-study-overview">
        <h3>Building Integration Layers for Product Teams</h3>
        <p class="meta">
          <strong>Full Stack Engineer</strong>
          Blue Cross NC &middot; Healthcare &middot; 2024-2025
        </p>
        <p>
          Designed an integration architecture that simplified complex service
          interactions and enabled frontend teams to move faster with fewer
          dependencies.
        </p>
        <p>
          Focused on reducing system friction while improving consistency,
          resilience, and delivery confidence.
        </p>
      </div>
      <div class="case-study-details">
        <div>
          <h4>Focus areas</h4>
          <div class="tags">
            <span class="tag">GraphQL</span>
            <span class="tag">Integration Architecture</span>
            <span class="tag">Feature Flags</span>
            <span class="tag">Vue</span>
            <span class="tag">Web Components</span>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div>
          <h4>Highlights</h4>
          <ul>
            <li>Introduced service abstraction patterns</li>
            <li>Reduced complexity across upstream integrations</li>
            <li>Improved deployment confidence through controlled releases</li>
            <li>Enabled cross-framework component strategies</li>
          </ul>
        </div>
      </div>
    </article>

    <article class="case-study">
      <div class="case-study-overview">
        <h3>Designing Interactive Decision Experiences</h3>
        <p class="meta">
          <strong>Frontend Engineer / UX Architect</strong>
          Aspida &middot; Financial Services / Insurance &middot; 2025-2026
        </p>
        <p>
          Created an interactive decision experience that transformed complex
          actuarial data into an approachable and engaging user journey.
        </p>
        <p>
          This engagement combined architecture, interaction design,
          visualization, and behavioral feedback systems.
        </p>
      </div>
      <div class="case-study-details">
        <div>
          <h4>Focus areas</h4>
          <div class="tags">
            <span class="tag">React</span>
            <span class="tag">State Machines</span>
            <span class="tag">Data Visualization</span>
            <span class="tag">Interaction Design</span>
            <span class="tag">Animation</span>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div>
          <h4>Highlights</h4>
          <ul>
            <li>Designed non-linear interaction flows</li>
            <li>Built resilient state management patterns</li>
            <li>Integrated animation as product feedback</li>
            <li>Balanced engagement with clarity and trust</li>
          </ul>
        </div>
      </div>
    </article>
  </section>

  <section class="work-method">
    <h2>How I work</h2>
    <p>
      The common thread across these engagements is not a specific framework or
      language. I focus on identifying constraints, simplifying complexity,
      aligning stakeholders, and creating systems that help teams move faster
      while improving outcomes for users.
    </p>
    <p>
      If any of these case studies connect with the problems your team is
      solving, I'd welcome a
      <a href="/contact">conversation</a>.
    </p>
  </section>
</Layout>

<style>
  /* ── Portfolio hero / intro ── */
  .portfolio-hero {
    margin-bottom: var(--space-section);
    padding-bottom: var(--space-component-lg);
    border-bottom: var(--size-border-pixel) solid var(--border-main);
  }

  /* Constrain hero text to readable width so the border below spans
     the same full width as .case-studies dividers */
  .portfolio-hero > * {
    max-width: var(--layout-max-width);
    margin-inline: auto;
  }

  .portfolio-hero h1 {
    margin-bottom: var(--space-sm);
  }

  .portfolio-hero .lede {
    font-size: var(--type-size-large);
    line-height: 1.55;
    color: var(--text-primary);
    margin-bottom: var(--space-sm);
  }

  .portfolio-hero p {
    margin-block: 0 var(--space-sm);
  }

  .portfolio-hero p:last-child {
    margin-bottom: 0;
  }

  .portfolio-note {
    color: var(--text-muted);
    font-size: var(--type-size-small);
    border-inline-start: 2px solid var(--brand-accent);
    padding-inline-start: var(--space-sm);
    margin-block-start: var(--space-md);
  }

  /* ── Case studies section wrapper ── */
  .case-studies {
    max-width: var(--layout-max-width-wide);
    margin-inline: auto;
  }

  .case-studies > h2 {
    margin-top: 0;
    margin-bottom: var(--space-md);
  }

  /* ── Individual case study card ── */
  .case-study {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: minmax(0, 1.2fr) minmax(17rem, 0.8fr);
    gap: var(--space-section);
    padding-block: var(--space-section);
    border-bottom: var(--size-border-pixel) solid var(--border-main);
  }

  .case-study h3,
  .case-study h4,
  .work-method h2 {
    margin-top: 0;
  }

  .case-study h3 {
    max-width: 20ch;
  }

  .case-study-details {
    display: grid;
    align-content: start;
    gap: var(--space-component-lg);
  }

  .case-study-details h4 {
    margin-bottom: var(--space-inline);
    font-size: var(--type-size-h5);
  }

  .tags {
    display: flex;
    flex-wrap: wrap;
    gap: var(--space-inline);
  }

  ul {
    padding-inline-start: 1.25em;
    margin: 0;
  }

  ul li {
    margin-bottom: var(--space-xs);
  }

  ul li::marker {
    color: var(--color-link);
  }

  .work-method {
    max-width: var(--layout-max-width);
    padding-top: var(--space-section);
  }

  @media (max-width: 800px) {
    .case-study {
      grid-template-columns: 1fr;
      gap: var(--space-component-lg);
    }
  }

  @media (max-width: 720px) {
    .portfolio-hero {
      margin-bottom: var(--space-component-lg);
    }

    .portfolio-note {
      margin-block-start: var(--space-sm);
    }
  }
</style>
